A N A C T
RELATING TO PUBLIC UTILITIES AND CARRIERS -- PUBLIC UTILITIES COMMISSION
Introduced By: Representatives Caldwell, Cotter, Stewart, Batista, McGaw, Morales,
Spears, and Kazarian
Date Introduced: February 28, 2025
Referred To: House Corporations
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 39-1 of the General Laws entitled "Public Utilities Commission" is
2 hereby amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 39-1-64. Cap on energy distribution fees.
4 (a) Notwithstanding any provisions of the general laws to the contrary, any public utility
5 as defined in ยง 39-1-2 shall not increase the transmission and distribution fees paid by the consumer
6 on a billing statement for a period of two (2) years commencing July 1, 2025, unless the increase
7 is approved by affirmative action of the general assembly.
8 (b) The provisions of this section shall not apply to a utility having fewer than seven
9 thousand five hundred (7,500) utility accounts.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
